sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction

Class CompartmentAbstractionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction.CompartmentAbstractionManager

  • public class CompartmentAbstractionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A CompartmentAbstractionManager provides functionalities for generation of AbstractCompartments, and their related AbstractSpecies, in an AbstractModel from the informations provided by a SBML Model.
    The CompartmentAbstractionManager works under the assumption that the SBML Model has been pre-processed with a ModelPreprocessingManager.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Method Detail

      • generateSpecies

        private AbstractSpecies generateSpecies(AbstractCompartment ac,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.Species s)
        This method generates an AbstractSpecies, that represents the given SBML Species, in the given AbstractCompartment, if it represents the SBML Compartment in which the given SBML Species is located.
        Note that after the call of this method, the generated AbstractSpecies encodes all the informations about the given SBML Species, except for the unit of measurement and the value.
        Parameters:
        ac - The AbstractCompartment in which the AbstractSpecies must be created.
        s - The SBML Species that must be represented by the AbstractSpecies.
        Returns:
        The generated AbstractSpecies.

      • computeSpeciesQuantityUnit

        private void computeSpeciesQuantityUnit(AbstractSpecies as,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.Species s)
        This method computes the UnitDefinition that represents the unit of measurement of the given SBML Species. The unit is then adjusted to match the reference to the amount or the concentration of the SBML Species and it is finally assigned to the given AbstractSpecies.
        Parameters:
        as - The AbstractSpecies that represents the SBML Species.
        s - The SBML Species that contains the informations about the unit of measurement.

      • computeCompartmentSizeUnit

        private void computeCompartmentSizeUnit(AbstractCompartment ac,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.Compartment c)
        This method computes the UnitDefinition that represents the unit of measurement of the size of the given SBML Compartment. The unit is then assigned to the given AbstractCompartment.
        Parameters:
        ac - The AbstractCompartment that represents the SBML Compartment.
        c - The SBML Compartment that contains the informations about the unit of measurement of its size.

      • generateCompartment

        private AbstractCompartment generateCompartment(org.sbml.jsbml.Compartment c)
        This method generates an AbstractCompartment, in the AbstractModel, that represents the given SBML Compartment.
        Note that after the call of this method, the generated AbstractCompartment only represents informations about the identifier, the name, the unit of measurement and the spatial dimensions of the given SBML Compartment. Furthermore, the method also generates the AbstractSpecies that represent the SBML Species whose the Compartment is represented by the generated AbstractCompartment.
        Parameters:
        c - The SBML Compartment that must be represented.
        Returns:
        The AbstractCompartment that represents the given SBML Compartment.

      • generateCompartmentsAndSpecies

        void generateCompartmentsAndSpecies()
        This method generates all the AbstractCompartments and their AbstractSpecies in the AbstractModel that represent the SBML Compartments and Species in the SBML Model.

      • computeSpeciesValue

        private void computeSpeciesValue(org.sbml.jsbml.Species s,
                                 AbstractSpecies as)
        This method computes an AbstractValue that represents the value of the given SBML Species in the SBML Model. The value computed by this method is according with the type of reference to the SBML Species.
        Once the AbstractValue has been computed, it is assigned to the given AbstractSpecies, that represents the given SBML Species.
        Parameters:
        s - The SBML Species that contains informations about the value.
        as - The AbstractSpecies that represents the given Species and whose the value must be computed.

      • computeCompartmentValue

        private void computeCompartmentValue(org.sbml.jsbml.Compartment c,
                                     AbstractCompartment ac)
        This method computes an AbstractValue that represents the value of the given SBML Compartment in the SBML Model and associates that AbstractValue with the given AbstractCompartment.
        Parameters:
        c - A SBML Compartment in the SBML Model.
        ac - An AbstractCompartment in the AbstractModel that represents the given SBML Compartment.

      • computeCompartmentsAndSpeciesValues

        void computeCompartmentsAndSpeciesValues()
        This method computes the AbstractValues that represent the values of the SBML Compartments and Species in the SBML Model and assign them to the AbstractCompartments and AbstractSpecies that represent them.
